        "originalName": "toolu_01SAbKniDf3NWtSY5RRXYzzD",
        "result": "# UCommandPalette API Summary\n\n## Groups Prop Structure\n\nThe `groups` prop accepts an array of objects with these properties:\n\n- **id** (string, required): Unique identifier for the group\n- **label** (string, optional): Display name for the group\n- **items** (CommandPaletteItem[], optional): Array of command objects\n- **slot** (string, optional): Custom slot identifier\n- **ignoreFilter** (boolean, optional): Disables internal search for custom filtering\n- **postFilter** (function, optional): \"Filter items after the search happened\"\n- **highlightedIcon** (string, optional): Icon when group is highlighted\n\n## Item Fields\n\nEach item in a group can include:\n\n- **label**: Command display text\n- **icon**: Icon identifier (e.g., 'i-lucide-file-plus')\n- **suffix**: Secondary text or description\n- **prefix**: Leading text\n- **kbds**: \"Array of keyboard shortcut strings or KbdProps objects\"\n- **onSelect**: Callback function triggered on selection\n- **children**: \"Array of objects with the following properties to create submenus\"\n- **avatar**, **chip**: Component-specific props\n- **active**, **loading**, **disabled**: State indicators\n\n## V-Model Usage\n\nControl selected values with:\n\n```vue\n<UCommandPalette \n  v-model=\"selectedValue\"\n  :groups=\"groups\"\n/>\n```\n\nFor multiple selections, pass an array to v-model or use the `multiple` prop.\n\nAccess the \"@update:model-value event to listen to the selected item(s).\"\n\n## Code Example: Grouped Commands\n\n```vue\nconst groups = [{\n  id: 'actions',\n  label: 'Actions',\n  items: [{\n    label: 'Add new file',\n    icon: 'i-lucide-file-plus',\n    kbds: ['meta', 'N'],\n    onSelect() { /* handler */ }\n  }]\n}]\n```",
        "success": true
      },
